{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:12:02.915Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"The extra `U201` warning is not a project-context problem anymore. It’s a duplicate-unit issue: local emits the same missing-library warning for both units of the same reference, while live KiCad only keeps the first one. I’m deduping that warning on the symbol-reference surface now, which is the narrowest upstream-compatible change for this case.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
