{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:20:59.627Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"The `TestPoint` mismatch is now concrete. The false local compare is coming from legacy property-surface noise that KiCad’s ERC compare ignores:\n- embedded has `Datasheet \"~\"` while the library has empty datasheet\n- the library has `Description` while the embedded copy effectively doesn’t\n- the embedded copy still carries property `id` atoms\n\nI’m grounding the fix on KiCad’s field compare path in `sch_field.cpp` now, because this is exactly the kind of legacy metadata noise `COMPARE_FLAGS::ERC` is supposed to normalize away.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:20:59.627Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"The `TestPoint` mismatch is now concrete. The false local compare is coming from legacy property-surface noise that KiCad’s ERC compare ignores:\n- embedded has `Datasheet \"~\"` while the library has empty datasheet\n- the library has `Description` while the embedded copy effectively doesn’t\n- the embedded copy still carries property `id` atoms\n\nI’m grounding the fix on KiCad’s field compare path in `sch_field.cpp` now, because this is exactly the kind of legacy metadata noise `COMPARE_FLAGS::ERC` is supposed to normalize away."}],"phase":"commentary"}}
