{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:27:06.174Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"I got the full serial suite run to completion so the real current frontier is explicit now. One clean unit was landed and committed as `8ace0f0` for `issue12814`; after that, the suite sits at `184 passed / 14 failed`.\n\nI also confirmed one thing I’m not going to fake-fix: `netlists/test_global_promotion/test_global_promotion.kicad_sch` is still upstream-ambiguous. Live KiCad omits the `R1` / `C1` symbol-mismatch and `C1` footprint-filter surface, so I left that alone and moved on.\n\nThe current concrete failure set from the real suite is:\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_hierarchical_component_classes_subsheet_1_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue10926_1_subsheet_1_1_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue14657_2_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue18092_sub_18092_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue18606_child_test_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue19646_f28p65x_osc_reset_debug_fixture_exactly`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue9367_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_no_connect_pins_connected_by_label_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_test_global_promotion_2_subsheet_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_test_hier_renaming_led_matrix_x6_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_top_level_hier_pins_fixture_exactly`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_top_level_hier_pins_subsheet_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_resolves_local_footprint_library_and_reports_filter_mismatch`\n- `schematic_erc_tracks_broad_hierarchical_kicad_qa_regression`\n\nI also started probing the `NoConnectOnLine` / `NoConnectOnPin` legacy `TestPoint` compare surface. There is one uncommitted experiment in [symbol.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/symbol.rs) to strip property `id` atoms from ERC signature normalization, but that alone did not close the `TestPoint` mismatch yet. The immediate next target I would take is the clustered hierarchy-label regression family (`issue10926_1_subsheet_1_1`, `issue14657_2`, `issue18606_child_test`, `top_level_hier_pins`), because those failures all show the same local pattern: missing upstream `isolated_pin_label`/subsheet label projection on standalone or shallow hierarchical roots.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
