il ERC is closed. Do not stop if you still have a full\n  upstream-qa parity merge request is ready. Do not stop after each case."}]},{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"Closed another maintained upstream-QA regression and kept it grounded to upstream KiCad shared-sheet behavior. The maintained exact count stays `117`.\n\nThe real fix is in [mod.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/mod.rs) and [hierarchy.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/hierarchy.rs). Concretely:\n- generated helper-power labels now stay recognized as generated after sheet text-variable expansion by matching both resolved `text` and original `raw_text`\n- repeated shared-child `multiple_net_names` warnings made only of hierarchical-label items are now coalesced onto the final repeated instance path, matching KiCad’s shared-screen reporting shape for `ERC_dynamic_power_symbol_test`\n\nThat closes [ERC_dynamic_power_symbol_test.kicad_sch](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/kicad/qa/data/eeschema/ERC_dynamic_power_symbol_test.kicad_sch) exactly against the stored upstream oracle and live `kicad-cli`. The upstream grounding here was [test_erc_hierarchical_schematics.cpp](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/kicad/qa/tests/eeschema/erc/test_erc_hierarchical_schematics.cpp), plus the standalone child behavior from [erc_test_dynamic_power_symbol_subsheet.kicad_sch](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/kicad/qa/data/eeschema/erc_test_dynamic_power_symbol_subsheet.kicad_sch), which already proved KiCad suppresses the local `REF${#}` helper-power conflict surface.\n\nVerification that passed:\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc dynamic_power_symbol -- --nocapture --test-threads=1`\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue10926_1_fixture -- --nocapture --test-threads=1`\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue18299_fixture -- --noca