{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:44:38.391Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"The label-only surface is deeper than one blanket condition. `issue16003` and `issue9367` are both showing that upstream’s `ercCheckLabels()` is making decisions per connection subgraph, not from our coarser resolved-net summary. I’m reading that upstream path directly now so I can patch the owning rule instead of stacking more local heuristics.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
