{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:48:33.620Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"I found the concrete bug. For shared-screen child `pin_not_connected`, we were picking the retained instance by largest reference text, but these KiCad fixtures are actually selecting the lexicographically first sheet-path instance. That matches both `R3` over `R4` in `sheet_3` and `R6` over `R5` in `another_sheet`, so I’m patching that path-based selection now and rechecking the whole family before committing.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:48:33.621Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"I found the concrete bug. For shared-screen child `pin_not_connected`, we were picking the retained instance by largest reference text, but these KiCad fixtures are actually selecting the lexicographically first sheet-path instance. That matches both `R3` over `R4` in `sheet_3` and `R6` over `R5` in `another_sheet`, so I’m patching that path-based selection now and rechecking the whole family before committing."}],"phase":"commentary"}}
{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:48:38.733Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"call_NMNDyDrkquNZhKcReQyTNU6H","name":"apply_patch","input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/hierarchy.rs\n@@\n fn shared_instance_pin_not_connected_is_non_primary(\n     violation: &PendingViolation,\n     schema: &crate::schematic::render::ParsedSchema,\n ) -> bool {\n@@\n-    let distinct_refs = symbol\n-        .instance_references\n-        .values()\n-        .collect::<BTreeSet<_>>();\n-\n-    if distinct_refs.len() <= 1 {\n+    if symbol.instance_references.len() <= 1 {\n         return false;\n     }\n \n-    let selected = distinct_refs\n-        .iter()\n-        .max_by(|lhs, rhs| cmp_reference_designators(lhs, rhs))\n-        .copied()\n-        .map_or(reference, |value| value.as_str());\n+    let selected = symbol\n+        .instance_references\n+        .iter()\n+        .min_by(|(lhs, _), (rhs, _)| lhs.cmp(rhs))\n+        .map(|(_, value)| value.as_str())\n+        .unwrap_or(reference);\n \n     reference != selected\n }\n*** End Patch\n"}}
