{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:49:13.547Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"The first-path heuristic was too broad; it fixed the standalone child but broke the full project’s second branch. The right upstream-shaped surface is narrower: for a parsed child schema, the active instance is already encoded in `symbol.reference`, so the shared-screen suppression should just keep the currently selected instance and suppress sibling refs, not recalculate a global winner.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:49:13.548Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"The first-path heuristic was too broad; it fixed the standalone child but broke the full project’s second branch. The right upstream-shaped surface is narrower: for a parsed child schema, the active instance is already encoded in `symbol.reference`, so the shared-screen suppression should just keep the currently selected instance and suppress sibling refs, not recalculate a global winner."}],"phase":"commentary"}}
