{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:53:58.303Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"The two no-connect surfaces are not contradictory after all. The difference is structural: the local parity oracle wants the directly overlapping pin when the no-connect is on a directly connected pin, while the upstream label-connected QA fixture wants the remote pin when the extra connection only arrives through a label-net neighbor. I’m restoring the direct-wire helper and making the selection conditional on whether the across-net candidate set is broader than the direct-wire set.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:53:58.304Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"The two no-connect surfaces are not contradictory after all. The difference is structural: the local parity oracle wants the directly overlapping pin when the no-connect is on a directly connected pin, while the upstream label-connected QA fixture wants the remote pin when the extra connection only arrives through a label-net neighbor. I’m restoring the direct-wire helper and making the selection conditional on whether the across-net candidate set is broader than the direct-wire set."}],"phase":"commentary"}}
{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:54:15.915Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"call_ykfejksoLRbvJNvSeuiMT2Ow","name":"apply_patch","input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/connectivity.rs\n@@\n pub(super) fn connected_pins_for_no_connect_across_nets(\n     point: Point,\n     schema: &ParsedSchema,\n     nets: &[ResolvedNet],\n ) -> Vec<PinNode> {\n@@\n     pins.dedup_by(|a, b| a.reference == b.reference && a.pin == b.pin);\n     pins\n }\n \n+pub(super) fn connected_pins_for_no_connect<'a>(\n+    point: Point,\n+    schema: &'a ParsedSchema,\n+) -> Vec<&'a PinNode> {\n+    if is_dangling_no_connect(point, schema) {\n+        return Vec::new();\n+    }\n+\n+    let mut frontier = vec![point];\n+    let mut visited_points = BTreeSet::from([point]);\n+\n+    while let Some(current) = frontier.pop() {\n+        for segment in &schema.wires {\n+            if !segment_connects_no_connect(current, segment, schema) {\n+                continue;\n+            }\n+\n+            for endpoint in [segment.a, segment.b] {\n+                if visited_points.insert(endpoint) {\n+                    frontier.push(endpoint);\n+                }\n+            }\n+        }\n+    }\n+\n+    let mut pins = schema\n+        .pin_nodes\n+        .iter()\n+        .filter(|pin| visited_points.contains(&pin.point))\n+        .collect::<Vec<_>>();\n+    pins.sort_by(|a, b| {\n+        a.reference\n+            .cmp(&b.reference)\n+            .then_with(|| a.pin.cmp(&b.pin))\n+            .then_with(|| a.order.cmp(&b.order))\n+    });\n+    pins.dedup_by(|a, b| a.reference == b.reference && a.pin == b.pin);\n+    pins\n+}\n+\n pub(super) fn unique_no_connect_pins_across_nets(\n     point: Point,\n     schema: &ParsedSchema,\n     nets: &[ResolvedNet],\n ) -> Vec<PinNode> {\n*** Update File: /Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schem