factor-wt/src/schematic/render.rs), embedded pins now carry KiCad-style pin physical position on the ERC surface instead of the old local pin-root approximation. That is the correct abstraction from upstream `SCH_SYMBOL::GetPinPhysicalPosition()` / `SCH_PIN::GetPosition()`.\n- In [project.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/project.rs) and [root.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/root.rs), standalone child schematics now use the parent project’s netclass assignments without inheriting the full parent project surface, including KiCad’s scalar `netclass_assignments` JSON form. That is what functionally closed the `issue14494_subsheet1` behavior gap.\n\nI also kept a serializer-parity improvement in [report.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/report.rs) and [mod.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/mod.rs): JSON positions are now rounded deterministically, and report ordering is now severity-first instead of type-sorted. That did not break the maintained exact guards I reran:\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue18092_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue1768_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue10926_1_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue18299_fixture`\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue13212_fixture`\n- `erc_parity_cases_manifest_is_well_formed`\n\nCurrent backlog state:\n- `issue14494_subsheet1` is functionally aligned with live `kicad-cli`; what remains is exact report ordering, not ERC logic.\n- `issue12814_2` is also down to report exactness, not rule behavior.\n- `issue20173/Kicad 9 - multi channel test.kicad_sch` is still open. The embedded-pin position fix was necessary, but not sufficient. The remaining mismatch is now isolated to shared-sheet symbol/connectivity semantics versus KiCad’s standalone handling, not generic wire logic.\n\nNo new upstream-QA case was safe to promote in this chunk, so the maintained exact count stays `110`."}],"phase":"final_answer"},{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Keep going. Always keep implementation and abstractions grounded to upstream code. You are an\n  autonomus agent, please keep working until ERC is closed. Do not stop if you still have a full\n  upstream-qa parity merge request is ready. Do not stop after each case."}]},{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"Promoted two more upstream-QA exact regressions into the maintained set:\n\n- `issue12814_2.kicad_sch`\n- `netlists/issue14494/issue14494_subsheet1.kicad_sch`\n\nThe supporting changes were already grounded to upstream KiCad behavior:\n- [project.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/project.rs) now handles KiCad’s scalar `netclass_assignments` form and uses the parent project only for assignment lookup on standalone child schematics.\n- [root.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/root.rs) now suppresses the root hierarchical-label `pin_not_connected` case on the same assignment surface KiCad uses.\n- [mod.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/mod.rs) and [report.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/report.rs) now round/report positions more deterministically, which helps the normalized parity surface the maintained tests actually compare.\n\nI added the exact tests in [cli_schematic_erc.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/tests/cli_schematic_erc.rs) and the manifest entries in [manifest.json](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/tests/fixtures/erc_upstream_qa/manifest.json). The maintained upstream-QA exact count is now `112`.\n\nVerification that passed:\n- `schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue12814_2_fixt