{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T23:00:36.183Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"The remaining regression is more specific than the first suppression: KiCad still projects child hierarchical labels with component pins behind them, but not the `issue14657` case where the child hier label is just a same-text local-label export. I’m narrowing the suppression to that exact upstream surface and restoring root single-pin reporting for true one-sheet-pin hierarchical labels.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T23:00:36.183Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"The remaining regression is more specific than the first suppression: KiCad still projects child hierarchical labels with component pins behind them, but not the `issue14657` case where the child hier label is just a same-text local-label export. I’m narrowing the suppression to that exact upstream surface and restoring root single-pin reporting for true one-sheet-pin hierarchical labels."}],"phase":"commentary"}}
